headline: 2 Dividend Stocks to Buy for Decades of Passive Income
summary: Healthcare giants AbbVie and Abbott Laboratories are both Dividend Kings.  In 2013, AbbVie (NYSE: ABBV) became a publicly traded corporation after splitting from its former parent company, Abbott Laboratories (NYSE: ABT).  AbbVie is a pharmaceutical leader with a large portfolio of approved products, none more important than a duo of immunology medicines: Skyrizi and Rinvoq.
